    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Problem description.</h3>\n<p>Siddharth was once browsing through the website of NIT Rourkela (Nitrkl). He was frustrated those days as he was not getting any idea to make questions for CodeNigma. Suddenly seeing the \"rkl\", an idea struck his mind. The idea goes like this:</p>\n<p>There is a special string of length N which is composed of letters \"r\", \"k\" and \"l\" only. He listed out all the possible strings of length N as per the above-mentioned condition. Then, he took each of the string one by one and performed the following operation:</p>\n<p>\n<ul>\n<li>List all the non-empty substring of the string</li>\n<li>Check for each substring that difference between the number of occurrences of x in the substring and the number of occurrences of y in the substring is less or equal to C. Note that: x and y can be any one of the 'r', 'k' or 'l'.</li>\n</p>\n<p>If the above condition is satisfied for all the substrings of a string, then he considers that string as a good string. Find the total number of good strings possible given the length N and C. Display the output after performing the modulo operation of it with 10<sup>9</sup> + 7.</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The input consists two space separated integers : <b>N C</b></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Display the number of possible good strings modulo 10<sup>9</sup>+7.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>(10<sup>9</sup>+7)</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>C</b> \u2264 <b>5</b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n3 1\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n6\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p>There are 6 possible ways: \"rkl\", \"rlk\", \"klr\", \"krl\", \"lrk\", \"lkr\".</p>",
